This paper deals with default reasoning, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). It also involves logic (cs.LO) and computational complexity (cs.CC) in defining the lexicographic closure. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of defaults in programming languages (cs.PL) and the analysis of cryptographic protocols (cs.CR).
